{
  "texts": [
    "TGNet designs the basic geometric unit TGConv to perform local convolution operations on point cloud data and combines the parameter pooling layer to aggregate TGConv features in the same local area.",
    "It generates new feature representations with rich contextual information for each point, significantly improving the performance of 3D point cloud segmentation.",
    "To efficiently process 3D point cloud data, (Lei et al. 2020) proposed a graph convolution method with a spherical kernel.",
    "This kernel systematically quantizes the local 3D space, identifies unique geometric relationships in the data, and extracts and integrates local features through defined pooling and non-pooling operations, providing strong support for fine geometry learning and weight sharing.",
    "Aiming at the disordered nature of point cloud data and the lack of local neighborhood information, (Shen et al. 2018) proposed the kernel correlation network (KCNet) model."
  ]
}